1 AN ACT
2 To amend and reenact R.S. 40:1567(A)(1)(a) and (B), relative to local fire departments; to
3 require a fire department to obtain an identification number from the National
4 Emergency Response Information System; to require reporting of all incidents; and
5 to provide for related matters.
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
7 Section 1. R.S. 40:1567(A)(1)(a) and (B) are hereby amended and reenacted to read
8 as follows:
9 §1567. Fire departments; fire department identification number; fire reports
10 A.(1)(a) Every municipal fire department, fire protection district, and
11 volunteer fire department, as recognized by its local governing authority, shall obtain
12 a fire department identification (FDID) number from the state fire marshal National
13 Emergency Response Information System.
14 * * *
15 B. Organizations which have been issued an FDID number shall submit
16 structural fire reports of all incidents electronically pursuant to the standards set by
17 the state fire marshal.
